===Pronunciation===
* [[IPA]] /'spunεrɪsm/

===Etymology===
Reverend W. A. Spooner (1844-1930), Dean and Warden of New College in Oxford, England, was said to have habitually made many of these phrases accidentally.

===Noun===
# A phrase, or pair of phrases, in which the first syllables (of at least one pair of words) are swapped.
''Tease my ears/Ease my tears''